                  "label": "Accordion",
                  "name": "widget_tokeny_faq_accordion",
                  "params": {
                    "accordions": [
                      {
                        "content": "<p>DALP is SettleMint's Digital Asset Lifecycle Platform for regulated financial institutions. For Italy, it provides Consob-aligned compliance controls, EU DLT Pilot Regime-compatible asset templates, MiCA-ready stablecoin infrastructure, and Italian data residency for tokenized asset operations.</p>",
                        "open_by_default": false,
                        "title": "What is DALP for Italy?"
                      },
                      {
                        "content": "<p>DALP provides infrastructure compatible with the EU DLT Pilot Regime: bond and equity templates with full lifecycle logic for tokenized securities issuance, transfer, and servicing under the Consob-supervised DLT framework, including automated coupon payments, redemptions, and corporate actions.</p>",
                        "open_by_default": false,
                        "title": "Does DALP support the EU DLT Pilot Regime for Italian institutions?"
                      },
                      {
                        "content": "<p>DALP enforces compliance ex-ante: 12 on-chain compliance module types cover Consob investor eligibility, transfer restrictions, country-based controls, and MiCA ART/EMT issuer requirements. Every transfer is validated against policy before execution, not reviewed after the fact.</p>",
                        "open_by_default": false,
                        "title": "How does DALP support Consob and MiCA compliance requirements?"
                      },
                      {
                        "content": "<p>Yes. DALP supports on-premises, Italian-hosted cloud, and hybrid deployment via Kubernetes and Helm. All data stays within Italy/EU for GDPR and Consob data sovereignty requirements. Deployment is fully configurable to meet Banca d'Italia IT governance standards.</p>",
                        "open_by_default": false,
                        "title": "Can DALP be deployed within Italian/EU data borders?"
                      }
                    ],
                    "css_class": "dnd-module",
                    "module_id": 362517245157,
                    "schema_version": 2
                  },
